profile_positions.description:
Registrar at the ISHSS (International School for Humanties and Social Sciences).

I started out as assistant registrar and 6 months into the job I was promoted to registrar (this position can be viewed as a combination between head of the education administration office and student dean). 

I was responsible for the Registrar's department, incl. managing the assistant registrar; developing plans, procedures, rules and regulations and policies; organising graduation ceremonies and course registration processes; advising students and colleagues; communicating with domestic and foreign organisations; administrating the student loans for American students ("Stafford loans"); dealing with the financial implications of the education on offer; secretary to the Board of Examiners; complaints coordinator; taking care of other education administrative tasks. I reported directly to the Dean of the ISHSS.

Projects:
- member of the UvA/KUB/CapGemini projectteam for replacement of the university-wide database ISIS; 
- member of the projectgroup which dealt with buying a new database-application to replace the Access-database which was developed by the ISHSS itself.

Products and results: 
- weekly planning for the entire year for all tasks; 
- handbook for the department; 
- I became the UvA-expert on Stafford loans
